<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Welcomes U.S.-DPRK Agreements </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1301163394 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1513 GMT 13 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1301163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 13 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- As a 
result of numerous working meetings between the United States 
and the Democratic People's Republic of Korea the sides have 
reached some agreements in New York on the eve of a new year. 
The agreements concluded include the following as the United 
States agree to stop carrying out the "Team Spirit" military 
exercises while the North Korea to permit that control to be 
enforced by the UNO [UN organization] observers over its nuclear 
objects and start a dialogue with magate [as received] in this 
respect. 
  This was said in the statement released there today by a 
press officer of the Ministry of External Relations of Mongolia. 
  We are highly appreciating and welcoming the statement runs 
the fact that the both sides have arrived at an agreement on 
arranging by June, July of 1994 the third stage of negotiations 
at high level in order to conduct a comprehensive discussion of 
the nuclear problems of the Korean peninsula and consider the 
issue on normalizing the relationships between them. 
  The press officer noted the significance of urgent 
implementing of the above mentioned agreements for the sake of 
regulation in the spirit of consent the nuclear problems of the 
Korean peninsula and complicated military and political 
situation and wished a success in this cause. 

</TEXT>

