<F P=102>  SK1401092194 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2200 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1401092194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2200 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Anti-U.S. demonstrations were held in Moscow on 12 
January, the day U.S. President Clinton started his three-day 
visit to Russia. 
  Masses from all walks of life taking part in the 
demonstration carried red flags and slogans reading, "Deputies, 
do not yield to U.S. pressure!" "Bourgeois dictatorship will 
never get through!" and "We object to Clinton's visit!" 
  Demonstrators who gathered in front of a building of the 
State Duma of the Russian Federation Federal Assembly held up 
their fists and shouted slogans such as "Yankee, go home!" and 
"Punish murderers!" and marched toward the U.S. Embassy in 
Moscow. 
  After holding an anti-U.S. protest rally in front of the 
U.S. 
Embassy in Moscow, they headed to an office building of the 
Federation Council of the Russian Federation Federal Assembly, 
shouting slogans. 

