ideal and system," he said, and stressed: 
  "The Kim Yong-sam `regime' must refrain from obstructing a 
fair solution of the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula 
through DPRK- USA talks and take the road of national 
reconciliation and unity in response to the 10-point programme. 
  "The Association of Koreans in Japan for Peaceful 
Reunification will wage a more vigorous struggle to make 1994 a 
historic year in which a new phase of national reunification 
shall be opened for founding a pan-national unified state of 
confederacy form in the 90s," he said. 

