<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il's Contribution to Chuche Highlighted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1401104194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1010 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1401104194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Work That Made Undying Contribution To Development of </F>
Chuche-based Theory of Party Building" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, January 14 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN in a 
by- lined article today says that "Let Us Bring About 
Revolutionary Turn in Party Work To Meet the Requirement of the 
Present Situation", a classical work published by the dear 
leader Comrade Kim Chong-il on January 14, 1983, is a famous 
work which has made an undying contribution to a fundamental 
turnabout in the party work conforming to the requirements of 
the obtaining situation and the advancing revolution and 
development of the chuche-based theory of party building. 
  The most important idea propounded in the work is to 
continue 
to deepen the work of establishing the monolithic ideological 
system of the party and make the unity and cohesion of the party 
and the revolutionary ranks more unbreakable. 
  In the work, the dear leader expounded that to establish the 
monolithic ideological system of the party is a fundamental 
principle of building a working-class party and a permanent work 
which all the party organisations should always regard as its 
cardinal task. And he laid down questions of principle arising 
in further deepening the work of establishing the monolithic 
ideological system of the party. 
  He also indicated tasks and ways of closely rallying all the 
party members, cadres and working people around the party and 
the leader by intensifying the work with the people and stressed 
the need to strengthen party leadership over socialist economic 
construction. 
  The work emphatically urges all the officials to learn from 
the great leader's work method, which requires them to go down 
to the lower units constantly and share sweets and bitters with 
the masses, and thoroughly apply it to practice. 
  Recalling that the validity and vitality of the idea, theory 
and policies laid down in the work have been fully proved in the 
revolutionary practice in the past, the author of the article 
says: 
  The work of establishing the monolithic ideological system 
of 
the party has been further deepened, the fighting capacity and 
leading role of the party have increased remarkably and the 
singlehearted unity of the revolutionary ranks with the 
illustrious leader at the centre has been consolidated further 
still in keeping with the requirements of the developing 
revolution in which the modelling of the whole society on the 
chuche idea has developed to a new, higher stage. 

</TEXT>

