<H3> <TI>   Swiss Committee Publishes `Korea Is One' Bulletin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1301103594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1013 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1301103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 13 (KCNA) -- The Swiss committee 
for supporting Korea's reunification published Korea-bulletin 
"Korea Is One". 
  The bulletin carries a photograph of the great leader 
President Kim Il-song receiving bereaved families of 
anti-Japanese revolutionary martyrs and introduces his 
reminiscences "With the Century". 
  In an article titled "For Nuclear-Free Korea", the bulletin 
notes that the purpose sought by the United States in its 
clamour about "nuclear inspection" is to detract the world's 
attention from its nuclear weapons in South Korea. 
  Saying that there is no ground for the DPRK to allow 
inspection of even the military base which has no nuclear 
facilities, it stresses that all the anti-imperialist 
peace-loving forces must extend support to the Korean people who 
are striving to realise the denuclearization of the Korean 
peninsula, get the U.S. forces withdrawn from South Korea and 
achieve the independent and peaceful Reunification of the 
country. 

</TEXT>

