<F P=102>  SK1401043894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0424 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1401043894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 14 (KCNA) -- The 27th plenary 
meeting of the Central Committee of the General Federation of 
Trade Unions of Korea held in Pyongyang on January 12 and 13 
discussed tasks for the trade union organizations to carry out 
the tasks set by the great leader President Kim Il-song in his 
new year address and implement to the letter the resolution of 
the 21st plenary meeting of the sixth Central Committee of the 
Workers' Party of Korea and the teachings given recently by the 
dear leader Comrade Kim Chong- il. 
  The meeting stressed the need for the trade union 
organizations to energetically organize the working class and 
other union members for the implementation of the party's 
revolutionary economic strategy of following the 
agriculture-first, light industry-first and trade-first policy. 
  Noting that Comrade Kim Chong-il recently said the working 
people's organizations should push ahead more vigorously with 
the work of human remoulding and indicated the ways to this end, 
the meeting emphasized that the trade union officials should 
conduct ideological education among the unionists well. 

