<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pyongyang Radio on Session </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1401093894 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2300 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1401093894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2300 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The 27th Plenary Session of the Central Committee of 
the General Federation of Trade Union of Korea [GFTUK] was held 
in Pyongyang on 12 and 13 January. The plenary session was 
attended by members and candidate members of the GFTUK Central 
Committee and chairmen of the trade unions of major plants and 
enterprises in provinces and cities. 
  The plenary discussed the task elucidated by the great 
leader 
Comrade Kim Il-song in this New Year's address, the trade union 
organizations' task to thoroughly implement the decision of the 
21st plenary session of the Sixth party Central Committee, and 
the trade union organizations' task to thoroughly implement the 
dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il's recent remarks. 
  Chu Song-il, chairman of the GFTUK Central Committee, made a 
report on the first agenda item. Following this, discussions 
were held. 
  The reporter and those who participated in the discussions 
stressed: In this New Year's address and in the 21st plenary 
session of the Sixth party Central Committee, the great leader 
Comrade Kim Il-song summed up the brilliant victory won by our 
people in socialist construction by firmly uniting around the 
party as one mind to repel all kinds of imperialists' challenges 
and, thus, safeguarding and defending socialism of our own style. 
  They noted the fact that in the Third Seven-Year Plan period 
the might of our working class' and working people's loyalty to 
the party and the leader [suryong], that is, the might of the 
singlehearted unity of the leader, the party, and the masses was 
more clearly proven and that thanks to the promotion of the work 
of making the national economy chuche-oriented, modernized, and 
scientific the economic and material foundations of our own 
style socialism have been firmly deepened and the vitality of 
our self- reliant national economy has been demonstrated. 
  Noting that in this period the GFTUK outstandingly performed 
the honorable mission and duty as the reliable supporter and 
defender of the party, the reporter and those who participated 
in the discussions mentioned the successes registered in the 
GFTUK's work under the wise leadership of the party. They 
stressed that today the trade union organizations are faced with 
the honorable work of contributing to safeguarding and defending 
socialism of our own style and to further adding luster to it. 
  The great leader Comrade Kim Il-song has taught: We should 
consolidate and develop the successes already registered in 
socialist construction and achieve a new greater victory so that 
we cannot only add luster to the popular masses-centered 
socialism of our country, but also fly higher the banner of 
socialism of chuche. 
  The reporter and those who participated in the discussions 
stressed that the trade union organizations at all levels should 
vigorously struggle to implement the party's strategies of 
pursuing the agriculture-first, light industry-first, and 
trade-first policies in socialist economic construction while 
designating two to three years to come as an readjusting period. 
  Saying that the ideological revolution should be 
strengthened 
among trade union members, the reporter and those who 
participated in the discussions presented detailed measures to 
wage ideological indoctrination work, including indoctrination 
in the principles of the chuche idea, indoctrination in the 
greatness of the idea, indoctrination in the revolutionary 
traditions, and indoctrination in the class character, through 
various forms and methods and in a substantial manner. They then 
stressed that all trade union members should deeply master the 
greatness of the respected and beloved leader's and the leader 
comrade leader's ideologies and theories, the greatness of their 
leadership, and greatness of their features and should be loyal 
to the party and the leader [suryong] under all circumstances. 
  They also stressed the need for trade union organizations to 
vigorously organize and mobilize working class and trade union 
members into the implementation of the party's revolutionary 
economic strategies. They noted that members of the trade unions 
at all levels should vigorously wage economic propaganda 
activities and carry out mass movements, including the socialist 
emulation movement, in a substantial manner, and, thus, should 
see to it that trade union members can vigorously advance in the 
spirit of adding the speed of the battle of Chollima so that all 
plants and enterprises can overfulfill this year's national 
economic plans. 
  The reporter and those who participated in the discussions 
stressed the need for trade union members to contribute to 
further strengthening the singlehearted unity of the leader 
[suryong], the party, and the masses by enhancing the function 
and role of their organizations and to effect a new upsurge in 
socialist construction. 
  A report and discussions were made on the second agenda 
items 
at the plenary session. 
  The reporter and those who participated in the discussions 
noted that the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il has recently 
elucidated the task that public organizations should further 
grasp human remolding work and the methods for its 
implementation. They stressed that functionaries of all trade 
union organizations should properly carry out ideological 
indoctrination work among trade union members in conformity with 
specific circumstances. 
  Saying that indoctrination to influence people by positive 
example is a mighty indoctrination method in line with the 
essence of the socialist society, the reporter and those who 
participated in the discussions stressed the need to strengthen 
indoctrination work through the examples set by forerunners in 
the laudable communist virtues. They also stressed that [words 
indistinct] should become a work with trade union members, the 
guidance of the organizational and ideological life of trade 
union members should be further strengthened, primary 
organizations of the GFTUK should be firmly built, and the 
movement to create model primary GFTUK organizations should be 
strengthened so that the ranks of trade unions can be further 
strengthened. 
  The reporter and those who participated in the discussions 
noted that by cherishing boundless loyalty to the party and the 
leader [suryong] and more properly carrying out human remolding 
work in conformity with the demands of the developing realities, 
all trade union functionaries should inspire revolutionary zeal 
and creative positiveness among the masses so as to achieve high 
successes in the implementation of the decision of the 21st 
plenary session of the Sixth party Central Committee. The 
session adopted a relevant decision. 

</TEXT>

