<F P=101> Malaysia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Suharto Offers Presidential Helicopter </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1401080694 Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA in English 0712 GMT 14 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1401080694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jakarta, Jan 14 (OANA-BERNAMA) -- President Suharto 
has offered a Super Puma helicopter used by the presidential 
palace to Malaysia for the use of Prime Minister Dr. Mahathir 
Mohamed and his deputy, Anwar Ibrahim; 
  The offer was made by Suharto when Anwar paid a courtesy 
call 
on him yesterday in conjunction with his two-day visit here, 
Anwar told Malaysian reporters Friday. 
  The offer is very touching indeed, he said before leaving 
for 
home in an RMAF [Royal Malaysian Air Force] aircraft. 
  Malaysia bought a Super Puma from Industri Pesawat Terbang 
Nusantara (IPTN) [National Aircraft Industry] in 1989 for VIP 
use. 
  The helicopter crashed in Sungai Petani, Kedah, two weeks 
ago 
while on its way to pick up Anwar in Kangar. 
  Science, Research and Technology Minister B.J Habibie, who 
heads the IPTN, also offered to provide the crew for the 
aircraft. 
  Anwar said Habibie felt that initially, the Indonesian crew 
might be useful. 
  He said he informed Suharto and Habibie that the offer was 
very touching and Malaysia welcomed it. 
  Anwar said he would brief Dr. Mahathir on the offer for 
follow up action. 

</TEXT>

