<H3> <TI>   New Deputy Finance Minister Sworn In 12 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1201153294 Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network in Malay 
1300 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1201153294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Malay </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Senator Mustapha Mohamed was sworn in as the new 
deputy finance minister before Paramount Ruler Sultan Azlan Shah 
at the National Palace in Kuala Lumpur today. Present at the 
ceremony were Datuk Sri Dr. Mahathir Mohamed, prime minister; 
Tun Hamid Omar, lord president of the federal courts of 
Malaysia; Attorney General Datuk Mokhtar Abdullah; Rahim Mohamed 
Noor, deputy inspector general of police; Tan Sri Ahmad Sarji 
Abdul Hamid, chief secretary to the government. 
  The appointment of Senator Mustapha, 44, was announced by 
Dr. 
Mahathir after the later chaired the UMNO [United Malays 
national Organization] Supreme Council meeting last Saturday. 
Senator Mustapha is replacing Mr. Abdul Ghani Othman, who has 
now been appointed youth and sports minister. Mustapha was 
appointed senator in 1991, which made him eligible to be 
appointed the parliamentary secretary of the Finance Ministry. 

</TEXT>

