<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   MNLF: Iran's Islamic Jihad Not in Mindanao </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1401055894 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 
14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1401055894 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City Radio Filipinas </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A prominent Muslim leader denied the existence of 
an Islamic jihad in the Philippines. MNLF [Moro National 
Liberation Front] Reformist Group Chief, Makapanton Abbas says 
they have not heard any local chapter of the Islamic jihad, a 
group formed by Iranian extremist during the civil war in 
Lebanon. The group which claimed responsibility for the 
bombings in Davao City had called itself Islamic Jihad. Abbas 
maintains that rightist military elements are behind the bomb 
attacks. 

</TEXT>

