<H3> <TI>   `Sisterhood Relations' Viewed With PRC Province </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1401104094 Seoul YONHAP in English 0807 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1401104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cheju, South Korea, Jan. 14 (YONHAP) -- The island 
province of Cheju will exchange a memorandum of understanding on 
a meeting to establish friendly relations with the Chinese 
province of Hainan, officials said Friday. 
  A delegation of nine officials and 13 businessmen from the 
Chinese province arrived in Cheju on Friday afternoon to discuss 
the establishment of sisterhood relations. 
  Governor Sin Ku-pum and Vice Governor Wang Sufeng, head of 
the delegation, discussed ways to form sisterhood relations 
between the provincial governments on Friday afternoon. 
  Wang plans to visit the provincial government office on 
Saturday to meet with Vice Governor Yi Man-ni to sign and 
exchange the memorandum. 
  The memorandum says that the two provincial governments 
agree 
that maintaining friendly and cooperative relations between the 
governments and populations and promoting mutual relations based 
on the principle of equality and reciprocity will be profitable 
for both governments. 
  The two sides decided to form sisterhood relations at an 
early date after recognizing the necessity of such relations. 

</TEXT>

