<F P=103> SK1401021194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul THE KOREA HERALD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Prosecutor-General's Office will set up a new 
department to deal mainly with international criminal affairs, a 
spokesman said yesterday. 
  The prosecution will also appoint a prosecutor at each 
district prosecution office who will exclusively handle crimes 
by foreigners, international disputes over intellectual property 
rights, and criminal affairs related to tariff and foreign 
currencies, he said. 
