<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> January </F>
<H3> <TI>   MAFF Official Criticizes U.S., Europe on Trade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1401125594 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 14 Jan 
94 Morning Edition p 5--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1401125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At quadrilateral trade talks among the United 
States, Japan, Canada, and European nations, the United States 
and European nations have called for starting renegotiations on 
some portions of agreements reached under the (Uruguay Round of 
GATT's) multilateral trade talks. In this connection, speaking 
at a news conference on 13 January, Vice Minister Kyogoku of the 
Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries [MAFF] 
criticized the moves of the United States and European nations, 
saying: "This is outrageous, and we cannot accept their 
requests." 
  Regarding trade issues involving the ministry, the United 
States is calling on Japan to make further concessions to lower 
a tariff rate for wood products. Vice Minister Kyogoku said "we 
have already confirmed with the United States that negotiations 
were concluded," thus reiterating that Japan has no intention of 
renegotiating the trade issues. 

</TEXT>

