<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Accord Signed With Japan on Infrastructure Aid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1401065294 Phnom Penh AKP in French 0415 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1401065294 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh 14 Jan (AKP) -- An agreement on Japanese 
aid to Cambodia was signed on 11 January in Phnom Penh by Prince 
Norodom Sirivut, deputy prime minister and minister of foreign 
affairs and international cooperation, and Katsuhiro Shinohawa, 
acting charge d'affaires of Japan in Cambodia. 
  According to this agreement, Japan will provide Cambodia 
with 
$9 million. The first installment of the aid is for the 
restoration of the "ODEM" [expansion unknown) bridge and the 
road building center and for the waterworks in Phnom Penh. 
  On this occasion, Prince Norodom Sirivut deeply thanked 
Japan 
for assisting in the restoration of roads and bridges, 
electricity, and drinking water in Cambodia. 
  For his part, Katsuhiro Shinahawa said the second 
installment 
of aid for a $25-million project will arrive in Cambodia this 
year in which $20 million will be designated for drinking water, 
with the remaining for bridges and roads. 

</TEXT>

