<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Larson Arrives for Talks on MIA Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1701071394 Hanoi VNA in English 0637 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1701071394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Jan. 17 -- Admiral Charles R. Larson, 
commander-in-chief of US Pacific Command, arrived here on Sunday 
for a three-day visit to Vietnam. He is the most senior US 
active-duty officer to visit since the end of the Vietnam War in 
1975. 
  Larson's visit is aimed at getting more first-hand 
information about Vietnam and about the MIA issue. 
  Yesterday afternoon, Admiral Larson and his entourage were 
received by Vietnamese Deputy Minister of Defence Nguyen Thoi 
Bung who reaffirmed that Vietnam regarded, the MIA issue as a 
humanitarian one. `No matter how', said Deputy Minister Bung, 
`the relations between the United States and Vietnam are 
developing, Vietnam would always actively cooperate with the US 
in the MIA issue'. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-47743 </DOCNO>
