<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Questions Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1801032594 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2330 GMT 18 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1801032594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The government has asked Russia whether the recent 
foreign news report stating that it has decided to sell 
additional submarines to North Korea is true. 
  Paek Nak-wan, director-general for the European Affairs 
Bureau of the Foreign Ministry, called a Russian minister to the 
ROK to the Foreign Ministry today and asked him to reveal 
whether the foreign news report stating that Russia had sold the 
four Fox-Trot submarines to North Korea and that it has recently 
concluded a contract to sell 10 additional Golf-class submarines 
to North Korea is true. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-47847 </DOCNO>
