<H3> <TI>   Ranariddh, Hun Sen See PRC President Jiang </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2001052194 Phnom Penh AKP in English 0409 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2001052194 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh AKP January 20 -- Co-Prime Ministers 
Prince Norodom Ranariddh and Hun Sen met in Beijing Tuesday [18 
January] with Chinese President Jiang Zemin. 
  During talks, Jiang informed the Cambodian prime minsters of 
the ties of friendship and cooperation between the two countries 
and peoples and of the works of national construction being 
carried out in China. 
  Prince Norodom Ranariddh who is in Beijing for the first 
time 
together with Hun Sen since the formation of the new government 
in November last year expressed thanks to the Chinese government 
for its active contribution to the peace process and national 
reconciliation in Cambodia. 
  He also praised the Chinese president for his clear-sighted 
leadership in all-sided development, especially in the field of 
economy. 
  The meeting was held after wreath-laid ceremonies at the 
monument for memorial of fallen combatants and at the Mao Zedong 
mausoleum and after the visit of sewing and freezer-producing 
factories. 

