<H3> <TI>   Report on Route 68 Operations, Pol Saroeun </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2001040994 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2001040994 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] During the past few days, many Vietnamese puppet 
forces that the puppet ringleaders sent to attack the people and 
Democratic Kampuchea forces on Route 68 were killed or wounded. 
Almost all of the survivors, who were in total panic, deserted 
the battlefield. 
  Seeing that the first, second, and third groups of his 
assaulting forces were beaten and dispersed, Pol Saroeun, the 
Vietnamese puppets' general staff commander, ordered 500 
soldiers from the Kompong Cham provincial unit to rescue their 
colleagues on Route 68. However, he could mobilize only 300 of 
them. However, nearly 100 of these forces fled while they were 
sent by truck to this area. 
  Between 15 and 18 January, these assaulting forces tried to 
launch an onslaught, but all their attempts were smashed by our 
mine attacks. Many of them were killed or wounded, and their 
trucks and armored personnel carriers were destroyed. All the 
wounded were in despair, waiting only for their dying day. 
  On 16 and 17 January, six trucks hit land mines and were 
shot 
at and destroyed in an area east of Samraong District. 
Fifty-six puppet soldiers were killed, 62 others were wounded, 
and 180 others deserted the battlefield. A major general from 
the engineering unit [name indistinct] and 12 colonels, majors, 
and captains were among those killed. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

