<DOCNO> FBIS3-47869 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas014__a94013" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-014-A </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  21 January 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Economic Framework Talks With U.S. </TI></H3>
<H4>   Obstacle of Numerical Targets </H4>
<F P=102> OW1901125094 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 19 Jan 94 
Morning Edition p 9--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1901125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A top official of the Ministry of International 
Trade and Industry said on 18 January that Japan-U.S. accord on 
the economic framework talks may be postponed if the United 
States sticks to its demand for setting numerical targets. 
  The official said: "If the United States adheres to the 
numerical targets, the two nations are unlikely to reach an 
accord on the objective criteria during the Hosokawa-Clinton 
talks in February. In that case, the settlement of the issue 
should be postponed until the next [G-7] summit in summer." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

