<H3> <TI>   Defense Official Wants Surveillance Satellites </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1801101694 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 18 Jan 
94 Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1801101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Noboru Hoshuyama, director of the Defense Agency 
[DA] Director General's Secretariat, speaking at a 17 January 
news conference on DA plans to procure surveillance satellites, 
said: "On the prerequisite that there are no political 
constraints, it is desirable to have surveillance satellites 
from the standpoint of improving intelligence capabilities." He 
thus indicated hopes that the DA would have such satellites in 
the future. 
  Hoshuyama also admitted that "research and studies are being 
conducted on the usefulness of surveillance satellites" at 
various DA bureaus and departments and at staff offices of the 
Ground, Maritime, and Air Defense Forces. 

</TEXT>

