<H3> <TI>   MONTSAME Publishes Press Reviews </TI></H3>
<H4>   Review for 14 Jan </H4>
<F P=102> OW1401210594 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1844 GMT 14 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1401210594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 14 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
newspaper ARDIYN ERH publishes the answers of the president of 
Mongolia P. Ochirbat to the questions of the newspaper 
correspondent on the occasion of the Day of Constitution of 
Mongolia. 
  The president noted that the new Constitution legally 
consolidated achievements in democratization and renewal of the 
country, declared the legal basis for independence and 
sovereignty of the state, for the human rights and freedoms, 
formation of the new state system, transition of the country to 
market relations. As the president announced, in two years 
after the Constitution was adopted a big work has been done on 
realization of provisions of the Constitution. The president 
called the State Great Hural, government and other organs to 
work actively on intensification of the renewal processes. 
  As the newspaper informs, at yesterday's sitting of the 
State 
Great Hural session N. Bagabandi made a salutary speech, which 
was addressed to all citizens, on the occasion of the second 
anniversary of the new Constitution. The State Great Hural 
chairman noted that adoption of democratic Constitution has been 
an event of a turning importance in the country's history. 
  The newspaper carries an interview of its correspondent with 
the new chief of the State Security Central Department, 
Lieutenant Colonel D. Sandag. He notes that the basic functions 
of the department is intelligence and counterintelligence work, 
the state guarding. D. Sandag announces that the State Security 
Central Department will be engaged only in fulfilment of these 
tasks, but not to play a role of a political police. 
  The newspaper publishes the laws on struggle with smoking 
and 
on international agreements of Mongolia. 
  The newspaper HUMUUN BICHIG, which is regularly issued in 
the 
old Mongolian script, informs that on 22 January the first 
session of the society "for the Mongolian script" will be 
convened. The newspaper notes that at the congress discussed 
will be the issues of rendering assistance to revival of the 
Mongolian script, realization of the decisions of the government 
on using this script in official documents and business 
correspondence. 
  In an interview with the newspaper correspondent the deputy 
head of the society "for Mongolian script," poet T. Galsan 
stresses that despite the numerous bans the Mongolian script is 
living and at present is reviving thanks to the democratic 
changes taking place in the country. T. Galsan notes that 
mastering of the Mongolian script is a duty of every citizen, 
who thinks about his motherland. 
  The newspaper informs about organization of the next 
olympiad 
of the Mongolian language and the Mongolian script. The 
olympiad is organized every year in three stages. Among school 
children of the first and second forms the olympiad is organized 
on reading, among pupils of senior forms on writing. The final 
third stage of the olympiad will be held in April. 
  The newspaper continues publishing the lessons in the 
Mongolian script. 

</TEXT>

