94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1701165994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 17 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- In 
connection with a completing here autumn session of the Great 
State Parliament of Mongolia Deputy Chairman of the Parliament 
J. Gombojab has held a press conference for Mongolian and 
foreign newsmen. He said that the Mongolian Parliament has 
approved 19 new laws and made changes and amendments to the 12 
laws and issued 40 resolutions during the autumn session. 
  He admits that the Parliament has not succeeded to discuss 
all the laws scheduled to be considered at first which was 
connected with a lack of a conception of legislative initiative 
on the part of the Great State Hural and the insufficient 
quality of the draft laws themselves. A number of most 
significant laws of civil code including those on land and 
securities are being worked out in order to submit them to the 
Parliament during its autumn session. 

</TEXT>

