<H3> <TI>   Oil Products Liable for Import Duties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1701172594 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1415 GMT 17 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1701172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 17 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- On 
considering the draft law on making changes and amendments to 
the customs legislation today on the proposal of the director of 
the state "Mongol Neftimport" concern the Mongolian Parliament 
has included the oil products into the list of commodities 
liable to be imposed upon with customs duties. It means that 
henceforth in case of bringing oil products into the country all 
the organizations excepting the "Neftimport" concern should pay 
additionally 20 per cent of customs duties. 

</TEXT>

