<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Smuggling, Rustling Violate Border With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1701172994 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1427 GMT 17 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1701172994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 17 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
Mongolian-Russian border line continues to be violated in 
reference to its Mongolian-Tuvinian part with the purposes of 
smuggling and rustling. Only for the first half of the month 
since beginning of the current year the state frontier line has 
been crossed illegally from the Mongolian side by 26 residents 
of the Uvs Aymag in the western part of Mongolia. Nine of them 
being residents of the Tes Somon who were crossing the border 
for the purpose of searching their cattle stolen were given a 
terrible beating by Tuvinians and arrested in the Oshina 
settlement of the Tesham Region, Tuva. From the Tuvinian side a 
searching group consisting of representatives of competent 
organs including police and securities did not behave themselves 
properly during their stay on the Mongolian territory in 
particular, they have beaten some residents of the Zuungobi, 
Baruunturuun Somons of the Uvs Aymag and then run away back 
through the border. This is reported to the MONTSAME 
correspondent in the Uvs Aymag. 
  Such cases of crossing illegally the Mongolian-Tuvinian 
border line has been going on for a many years. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

