<H3> <TI>   Castro Sends Condolences for Phoumi Death </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2001120394 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 1200 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2001120394 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lao </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Telegram of condolences from Comrade Fidel Castro Ruz, </F>
first secretary of the Communist Party of Cuba Central 
Committee, president of the Council of State, and president of 
the Council of Ministers of the Republic of Cuba, to Comrade 
Khamtai Siphandon, chairman of the Lao People's Revolutionary 
Party [LPRP] Central Committee and prime minister of the Lao 
People's Democratic Republic [LPDR]; and Comrade Nouhak 
Phoumsavan, president of the LPDR, on the demise of Comrade 
Phoumi Vongvichit, adviser to the LPRP Central Committee -- date 
not given] 
  [Text] Beloved comrades: We are extremely saddened to be 
informed of the passing away of Comrade Phoumi Vongvichit. 
During the revolutionary movement, he established an 
unforgettably fine model practice in the history of the struggle 
of the courageous people. From that period, he devoted himself 
to the tasks against colonialism and imperialism for the sake of 
national independence. Comrade Phoumi Vongvichit always honestly 
adhered to his ideal of patriotism and [word indistinct]. This 
was shown during the highly responsible performance of his 
duties throughout the period when a new life for Laos was being 
created and the party and state were being built, as well as in 
other activities. The passing away of Comrade Phoumi Vongvichit 
means the Lao People's Revolutionary Party has lost an honest 
and virtuous senior citizen. It is also the loss of an intimate 
friend for the communists and people of Cuba. However, we are 
confident that the comrades who participated in the past 
struggles with him and the determined and courageous Lao people 
will carry on his tasks, to which he devoted himself throughout 
his life. 
  Through the comrades, we convey our deepest sorrow to the 
Party Central Committee, the government, and the people of Laos, 
as well as to his relatives and family. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

