<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Decision To Bar Mourners Decried </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2101110794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1039 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2101110794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 21 (KCNA) -- Paek In-chun, 
chairman of the North side headquarters of the National Alliance 
for the Country's Reunification, in his telephone message to the 
"minister of the unification board" of South Korea Thursday 
notified him that we were going to send a mourners' group to 
Seoul with a view to cherishing the memory of the Rev. Mun 
Ik-hwan, a patriotic champion for reunification, on his sudden 
death and sharing pains with the South Korean people, and 
proposed to have a contact between working officials of both 
sides at the conference room of the Neutral Nations Supervisory 
Commission at Panmunjom at 10:00 AM on January 21 to discuss 
working matters concerning it. 
  But the contact between the working officials of both sides 
failed to be held today owing to the unjustifiable attitude of 
the South side. 
  The South Korean authorities did not come out to contact 
without a reply telephone message, avoiding our compatriotic and 
courtesy proposal for a consolatory visit under an inhuman, 
illegal, unjust and unreasonable pretext contrary to common 
sense. 
  The North side representatives in Panmunjom of the 
North-South liaison office informed the South side of our stand 
concerning the contact at 09;00 this morning by telephone and 
urged it to come out to the contact but it evaded the contact, 
not saying a word. 
  The working officials of the North side failed to discuss 
the 
Seoul visit of our mourners' group with the South side and, 
accordingly, the group failed to go to Seoul and mourn the late 
Rev Mun Ik-hwan on January 22 [as received], the funeral day, as 
scheduled. 
  The behaviour of the South Korean authorities who refused to 
accept the North side mourner's group this time showed that they 
are not human beings, far from being the same nation, and they 
have neither ancestral manners and customs nor courtesy and 
morality. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

