<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paek Han-ki Makes Statement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2001042794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0411 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2001042794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, January 18 [dateline as received] (KNS-KCNA) 
-- Paek Han-ki, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee 
of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan, in a 
statement today bitterly denounced the anti-DPRK smear campaign 
of the Japanese authorities and urged them to stop the hostile 
acts at once. 
  The Japanese authorities recently launched a probe into a 
trading firm of Japan "suspected of violating the regulations of 
the Coordinating Committee for Multilateral Export Controls 
(Cocom)" and are conducting a despicable anti-DPRK campaign, 
connecting the case with the innocent DPRK in a far-fetched way. 
  The vice-chairman branded this as an utterly groundless 
fabrication to impair the dignity and prestige of the DPRK and 
another shameless political intrigue, which shows the true 
colour of the Japanese authorities who resort to hostile 
propaganda, reversing black and white. 
  He said: 
  "At a time when the DPRK and the United States are moving 
toward a package solution of the problems for a fundamental 
settlement of the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula thanks 
to the self-determined and aboveboard diplomatic policy of the 
DPRK, the Japanese authorities have launched a new smear 
campaign against the DPRK. This is an unpardonable challenge to 
throw a wet blanket over the progress of the DPRK-U.S. talks and 
isolate and blockade the DPRK. This is also an anachronistic 
act against the world public that wish the solution of the 
nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula and the improvement of the 
DPRK-U.S. relations through dialogue and negotiation. 
  "With no pressure and plot can the international 
reactionaries and the Japanese authorities undermine the 
international prestige of the DPRK or block the advance of the 
Korean people. 
  "The Japanese authorities must look straight at the trend of 
the times and immediately stop the smear campaign and hostile 
acts against the DPRK." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

