<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   South's Positioning of Gun Inside DMZ Alleged </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2001125294 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1216 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2001125294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1216 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The South Korean puppets today brought a 
large-caliber gun into the DMZ in the western front line, thus 
committing a grave military provocation. 
  At around 0920 today, the South Korean puppets illegally 
brought and installed a 105-mm large-caliber gun 1,800- meters 
east of the Military Demarcation Line [MDL] Marker 0038 in front 
of Tongchang-ri, Panmun County, Kaesong City, from the direction 
of Paengnyong-ri, Paju County. They assumed the firing position 
toward our side and gravely irritated us. 
  That the South Korean puppets openly brought a large-caliber 
gun into the DMZ in broad daylight is a preplanned provocation 
maneuver designed to artificially aggravate the situation in 
this area where armed forces of the two sides are being deployed 
acutely. 
  Since such military provocation is perpetrated at a time 
when 
the U.S. imperialists and bellicose elements in the puppet 
military recently made frequent visits to the areas in the 
foremost frontline and instigated the frenzy for northward 
invasion, we cannot overlook this provocation. 
  The South Korean puppets should correctly ponder the grave 
consequences to result from arms buildup maneuvers in the DMZ. 
They should not act rashly. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
